REMOVING FILE

1) rm f1.txt = to remove file empty file 

2) rm -r f1.txt = If you want to remove or delete a file along with its content

3) rm -rf f1.txt = If you want to remove or delete a file along with its content or maybe an empty file


REMOVING Directory 

rm folder1 - to remove empty folder 

rm -r folder1 - to remove the directory in which there is a folder in the folder 

rm -rf folder1 - to remove a directory along with recursive force 


note = we can not remove the directory forcefully we have to apply recursive force.
